  # Mobile Phone Price Classification

Predict phone price range (0-3) based on specifications

## Dataset

- 4020 phones total
- 3020 with price labels (training)
- 1000 without labels (predicted)
- Features: battery, RAM, memory, screen, cores, etc.

## Results

| Model | Accuracy |
|-------|----------|
| XGBoost | 93.7% |
| Random Forest | 92.1% |
| Logistic Regression | 91.4% |

## Key Insights

- RAM is strongest predictor (0.83 correlation)
- Battery power has moderate effect (0.30)
- Data imbalanced: 50% phones in mid-range

## Visualizations

![Correlation Matrix](correlation_matrix.png)
*Feature correlations show RAM dominates price prediction*

![Confusion Matrix](confusion_matrix.png)
*Model performs well across all price ranges*

## How to run
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python phone_classifier.py


Outputs:

Trained model in models/
Predictions in data/predicted_phone_prices.csv
Visualizations: correlation_matrix.png, confusion_matrix.png

EDA Notebook
Interactive exploration with Plotly: notebooks/phone_eda.ipynb